We recommended the following:
The Inventory Committee conduct an inventory of the local roads under the jurisdiction of the Municipality and render a Report on the Physical Count of the Road Network System;
The General Services Officer:
Render a Report               on Local Road Network and Road Map;
Regularly maintain and update the Registry of Public Infrastructures for Roads; and
Keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components; and
The Municipal Accountant:
Prepare and maintain a Local Road Network Ledger Card;
Keep and maintain subsidiary records for roads and road components for every road network; and
Prepare a lapsing schedule for the computation of the depreciation for each component at the end of the year.

We recommend the following:

1. The Municipal Mayor, representing Management, and EURAM, being the Negotiating Agent, update annually the CNA and not just for a one-time basis to better reflect the annual requirements stated in the General Appropriations Act and the related DBM Budget Circulars;

2. The Committee submits proof of the following:
a. That LGU-Ramon Magsaysay has achieved at least an average of 70% of all the targets under their PPAs as budgeted in CY 2019;
b. They have reviewed the agency’s financial records; and
c.    The written resolution indicating the MOOE Allotments that had become available as a result of cost-cutting and systems improvement measures and the internal guidelines governing the grant of CNA.

3. The grant of CNA be limited only to those covered under Item 3.0 of the Budget Circular, excluding the workers who have no employer-employee relationship with the LGU;

4. The Municipal Budget Officer and the Municipal Accountant use the correct account to record the grant and payment of the CNA; and

5. Municipal Mayor to stop the practice of granting CNA Incentive to its Municipal Officials and Employees until the policy and procedural guidelines on the granting of CNA Incentives are already complied with.

We recommended that the management:

Instruct the Accounting Department to:

Record in the appropriate inventory account all inventory account all purchases of supplies and materials upon acceptance of the delivered items, except those purchased out of the Petty Cash Fund;

Maintain the appropriates SLC for each item of stock/inventory and regularly prepare the SSMI based on the approved RIS and submit to the Accounting Department for the proper recording of books;

Record in the books of accounts, the cost of the issued/utilized supplies and materials contained in the Inventory Report; and

Apply the Perpetual Inventory Method of accounting for inventories.

Instruct the GSO/ Municipal Treasurer to:

Maintain the appropriate Stock Cards for each item of stock/inventory and regularly prepare the SSMI based on the approved RIS and submit to the Accounting Department for the proper recording in the books;

Effect regular reconciliation of the balances of the SC with the SLC of the Accounting Department; and 

Together with the committee created for the purpose, conduct annual physical inventory of all supplies and materials.

