We recommended the following: 

HRMO Upon hiring of personnel through JO Contracts, specifically stipulate in the contracts the duties and responsibilities of the personnel concerned and strictly observe and comply the established laws, rules and regulations on the documentation requirements before making any payment; 

direct the Department Heads in-charge to check and verify the Accomplishment Reports submitted by his personnel under his accountability vis-à-vis of his actual accomplishments; 

require the claimant to explain why there were no entries on the DTRs for time in and out before the Department Head or HRMO shall signed his/her DTR; and

direct the Municipal Accountant to ensure the correctness of the total actual services rendered per DTR consistent with the JO Contracts and per payroll, check the completeness of the supporting documents before signing the Disbursement Voucher and refrain from processing Disbursement Vouchers with incomplete documents. Should there be lacking supporting documents for the claim, the same shall be returned.

